The paper discusses Explainable Artificial Intelligence (XAI) and instance-level interpretability for complex machine learning models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper examines the behavior of popular instance-level explanations, which may involve statistical methods and algorithms, indicating that the paper may also belong to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper performs a large-scale benchmark, which may involve data analysis and statistical methods, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
